        "created_at": "2024-05-08T00:04:09.073Z",
        "cooked": "<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=3664193&amp;iNote=11132183\"><b>2018 Lamy-Caillat Bourgogne Blanc</b></a> - France, Burgundy, Bourgogne Blanc (5/7/2024)<br>\nRidiculously good for its level. Some smoky mineral reduction and citrus blossom. The palate has a sweet core of white peach. There's freshly grated ginger too. It is unctuous and silky of texture. The finish has citrus rind freshness and it persists. Entering a good drinking zone but still very fresh and vital.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/\">CellarTracker</a></p>",
